wikipedia_page.main: William "Wally" Webb (born 19 November 1882, date of death unknown) was a British bantamweight boxer who competed in the early twentieth century. He won a bronze medal in boxing at the 1908 Summer Olympics losing against John Condon in the semi-finals.
